  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Can't enter 18 digits after the comma for the 4-digit amount, for example, I want to send or request `1000,111111111111111111` tokens\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI am able to send any valid amount with the 18 digits limit after a comma, no matter how many digits before comma I have, for ex `1000,111111111111111111` . See also other 2 restrictions in comment https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4404#issuecomment-397707306\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe field is limited so entering `1000,111111111111111111`  is not possible\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open wallet\r\n- Having 2000 tokens try to send 1000,111111111111111111 \r\n- Try to request 1000,111111111111111111 \r\n",
